creator: Various
description: This is a collection of 25 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for June 2013. This project contains the following: April by Sharmel Iris (1889-1967) As I'd Nothing Else to Do by Herbert Fry (1830-1885) The Cremation of Sam McGee by Robert W. Service (1874-1958) The Enchanted Shirt by John Hay (1838-1905) The Fairest Land by Marietta Holley (1836-1926) If I Could But Forget by Paul Lawrence Dunbar (1872-1906) In Memory of a Happy Day in February by Anne Brontë (1820-1849) Judith by Maria Brooks (1794-1845) The Lady of Shalott by Alfred, Lord Tennyson (1809-1892) The Lament of Baba Tahir: being the Rubaiyat of Baba Tahir, Hamadani (Uryan) by Baba Tahir (d. 1020), translated by Elizabeth Curtis Brenton (1879-?) Life by Paul Lawrence Dunbar (1872-1906) Love Song by Harriet Monroe (1860-1936) Lycidas by John Milton (1608-1674) The Mystery of Gilgal by John Hay (1838-1905) Old by Paul Lawrence Dunbar (1872-1906) Patterns by Amy Lowell (1874-1925) The Pipes: Onset by Joseph Lee (1876-1949) The Purple Raven by Maurice Switzer (1870-1929) Reconciliation by Caroline A. Mason (1823-1890) The Seven Selves by Khalil Gibran (1883-1931) The Splendid Shilling: an Imitation of Milton by John Philips (1676-1709) Tennessee by Francis Brooks (1867-1889) To a Poet a Thousand Years Hence by James Elroy Flecker (1884-1915) Too Late by John Hay (1838-1905) The Voyage by Caroline A. Mason (1823-1890) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
